{
  "texts": [
    "Still, a stringent requirement remains: access to an exact classical simulation to obtain p(z), precluding direct fidelity estimation at large system sizes.",
    "We circumvent this constraint by introducing a method to estimate the fidelity by benchmarking against approximate classical simulations.",
    "We consider a comparison (Fig. 2b) between an ideal highentanglement target pure state, |ψ⟩, the experimental mixed state, ρexp, and a pure state from classical MPS simulation, Ψ ⟩ sim |.",
    "We introduce an improved MPS time-evolution algorithm using an optimal decomposition of Hamiltonian dynamics into quantum circuits 29, 30, which we term Lightcone-MPS (Supplementary Information).",
    "The MPS is parameterized by a bond dimension, χ, that defines the maximum simulable entanglement, which scales as χ log."
  ]
}